They were ok, they are very slow people in what they do. The food was kinda cold. They thought I didn’t know Spanish, so they talked behind my back. The tables are dirty, they don’t clean after you finish eating. I gave it a 2 because it was edible.

Went in to try the cheese slice and it was $2.50. Couldn't pay with credit card. I think you need to spend $7 before you can use credit.  The slice isn't even that big to cost so much. I know $1 pizza the tastes better. Not worth the price at all. Didn't have any flavor to me. I had to add seasonings. It's edible if it was the only option but I wouldn't return. Besides the service sucks. I got a burnt pizza and when I mentioned it, nothing was done to give me a better slice of discount. Just attitude and no apology. They shouldn't even be serving burnt pizza at all.

Fantastic!

Honestly, after months of late night dollar slices, you CANNOT go wrong with their regular cheese slice. It’s an AUTHENTIC ny slice. No frills. Crust is pretty close to perfect, cheese and grease are *kisses fingers*.  On the money. You’ll get your moneys worth.

Not very customer service like at all. I asked for one slice and he puts it in a bag fold it up and charges me, does not ask me if that's all?, if I would like a drink?, I take the pizza slice out the bag because I wanted to put garlic powder on it. I look at the slice and I say let me get another one please this might not fill me up,  and please put this one back in the oven. He takes the slice puts it in a box disregard my directions and the second slice I asked for throws it in the box sauce and cheese all over. Not buying from there again. Maybe I have to be white or a student of Columbia University.  Idk

Definitely the best pizza in the neighborhood. Simple, straightforward and good food. Prices are decent and the guys don't keep you waiting. If you're by Columbia and want pizza, you call Tom's, plain and simple.

I think this place has one of the best pizzas in town. Ive been coming here for over 10 years and they just do it right. Very cheesy, ny style pizza at its best. I usually get their balsamic vinegrette on the side to dip in for my crust. A must try.

Horrible. Order came late. Stale and thin pizza. Greasy. Cold. Awful. Garlic knots cold and stale as well. MozzeIla sticks semi decent. I ate here 2 years ago and pizza was excellent. Super disappointed. Hyped it up to friends and they were disappointed. Clearly my friends and their friends and so on will not eat this expensive nasty pizza. It feels like it was made with no care. Took one bite and had to throw all of it out and get Olgas on 138th street and broadway. Please stop lying and saying the food is great. I got food poisoning from here and the pizza is really inconsistent in the cheese and the sauce. At one point, this place had a "C" rating from having cockroaches and the ingredients being old. A "C" rating means quite frankly that they should be closed but got a second chance to turn things around.
This is for a pizza connoisseur.  One of the best slices in the city, and the best in the neighborhood.  I'm very glad they're nearby.
Service is good. Need to improve about taste
Pizza is nasty !  But I guess for a ten dollar med pie that's what you get
Delicious, cheap pizza. Try the chicken pizza!

My favorite delivery pizza in NYC. There's places to sit down for pies that are great, too, but delivery pizza is its own thing and Tom's is excellent. (They're also a great place to pick up a slice or two, which is also its own thing but more closely related to good delivery. It's a little bit about how the pizza reheats, but that's not the only thing. Some places with great takeaway slices are terrible for delivery. Tom's is good for both.)

Ordered a pepperoni pie with extra toppings, and the pizza I received didn't have any pepperoni -- and most of the cheese / other toppings were not *on* the pizza, but mostly shoved to one side of the pizza box. My "replacement" pizza was supposed to be delivered to me in an hour. TWO hours later... I hadn't received the pizza, and found out that the establishment was closed. Thankfully, I ordered through grubhub, and was refunded.  I won't order from this place either directly, or through grubhub ever again.
Great price, very fast delivery and delicious food!!! Highly recommended
Much of the food is very bland. I'd not recommend buying pizza with much vegetables. Something with extra cheese and meat can be decent. The pastas are practically flavorless; don't waste your time.
The best pizza in the town, and fast delivery .

I just called this place 4 times- the first 3 I was hung up on by a woman.....I was trying to place over a $500 order for a party I have this Saturday, and since i asked for a manager or owner- the staff thought I was soliciting and hung up on me- 3 TIMES!! When I tried to call back, they didn't pick up the phone. I called again and a man picked up, asking to take my order....after i was hung up on 3 times and ignored once. what a joke  I GUESS THIS PLACE DOESN'T NEED THE BUSINESS.
